<tr class="even areaheader  firstrow"><td colspan="2"><span class="courselistcomment areaheader ">Program Requirements</span></td><td class="hourscol"></td></tr>
<tr class="odd"><td colspan="2"><span class="courselistcomment">120 hours are required for the degree. Approved plans of study for the Major in Liberal Studies must include the following:</span></td><td class="hourscol"></td></tr>
<tr class="even"><td colspan="2"><div style="margin-left:20px;" class="blockindent"><span class="courselistcomment commentindent">• At least 30 (and no more than 40) semester hours for the major</span></div></td><td class="hourscol"></td></tr>
<tr class="odd"><td colspan="2"><div style="margin-left:20px;" class="blockindent"><span class="courselistcomment commentindent">• An established UIC minor in its entirety, along with additional relevant and complementary courses</span></div></td><td class="hourscol"></td></tr>
<tr class="even"><td colspan="2"><div style="margin-left:20px;" class="blockindent"><span class="courselistcomment commentindent">•  A minimum of 18 hours of advanced course work, of which at least 6 hours must be at the 300 level</span></div></td><td class="hourscol"></td></tr>
<tr class="odd"><td colspan="2"><div style="margin-left:20px;" class="blockindent"><span class="courselistcomment commentindent">• A course in the student's minor department that is designated to satisfy the Writing-in-the-Discipline requirement; alternatively, an appropriate Writing-in-the-Discipline course from another department or program must be proposed and approved.</span></div></td><td class="hourscol"></td></tr>
<tr class="even"><td colspan="2"><span class="courselistcomment">Students in the Liberal Studies major are also required to:</span></td><td class="hourscol"></td></tr>
<tr class="odd"><td colspan="2"><div style="margin-left:20px;" class="blockindent"><span class="courselistcomment commentindent">•  Complete all UIC and LAS requirements for graduation</span></div></td><td class="hourscol"></td></tr>
<tr class="even"><td colspan="2"><div style="margin-left:20px;" class="blockindent"><span class="courselistcomment commentindent">•  Meet with their faculty mentor at least once each term</span></div></td><td class="hourscol"></td></tr>
<tr class="odd"><td colspan="2"><div style="margin-left:20px;" class="blockindent"><span class="courselistcomment commentindent">•  Meet with their assigned LAS academic advisor at least once each term</span></div></td><td class="hourscol"></td></tr>
<tr class="even lastrow"><td colspan="2"><div style="margin-left:20px;" class="blockindent"><span class="courselistcomment commentindent">•  Meet at least once with an advisor at the LAS Career Development Office to establish a plan for the use of on-campus preprofessional resources and internship opportunities.</span></div></td><td class="hourscol"></td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<p><strong>Note:</strong> Revisions to the approved plan of study must be supervised by the student's faculty mentor and approved by the LAS Associate Dean for Student Academic Affairs. The academic advisor will document these approvals. Students must seek approval for such revisions prior to enrolling in the relevant course.</p>
<p>Students will not be allowed to major in both an existing major and the Major in Liberal Studies.</p></div><!--end #textcontainer -->



